#!/usr/bin/env O
# STEP-4: first-class coordination primitives.
#
# A Group makes the EXECUTION TOPOLOGY of several computations explicit in
# the value model. Where a Request names a single deferred computation, a
# Group names a collection of them together with a mode that says HOW they
# relate:
#
#   batch(a, b, ...)  — run them together for throughput; yields every result
#   all(a, b, ...)    — fan-out, every member must succeed; yields every result
#   any(a, b, ...)    — redundancy/fallback; yields the first member to succeed
#   race(a, b, ...)   — latency competition; yields the first member to settle
#
# A Group performs no work on its own. It is forced by `now(group)`, by
# `autonomous(group)`, or at document end under Autonomous policy.
#
# MVP NOTE: the runtime is synchronous (no async, no Tokio, no cancellation),
# so `any` and `race` both resolve members left-to-right and return the first
# success. The mode is preserved in the value so a future concurrent scheduler
# can honour the true topology.

# ── Group over plain values (runs without Nix) ───────────────────────────────
# nix_expr^ produces a NixExpr value WITHOUT invoking Nix, so this section is
# self-contained: it shows the topology over already-constructed values.
let e1 = nix_expr^( pkgs.hello )_nix_expr
let e2 = nix_expr^( pkgs.cowsay )_nix_expr
let e3 = nix_expr^( pkgs.figlet )_nix_expr

# batch(...) bundles the three expressions into one Group value.
let bundle = batch($e1, $e2, $e3)

# now(group) forces the group per its mode. Batch collects ALL members, so the
# result is an OList of the three values, in order.
let collected = now($bundle)

# any(...) yields the FIRST member (single winner), not a list.
let first = now(any($e1, $e2, $e3))

# ── Group over deferred Requests (needs a working Nix; commented) ─────────────
# Under lazy(...) the inner instantiate/realise Requests are constructed but
# NOT performed, so the batch holds three unforced Request chains. now($builds)
# then forces them all and returns a list of StorePaths.
#
#let builds = lazy(batch(
#    realise(instantiate($e1)),
#    realise(instantiate($e2)),
#    realise(instantiate($e3))
#))
#let paths = now($builds)
#
# autonomous(batch(...)) is the MVP scheduler integration: the inner Requests
# are buffered, the scheduler dispatches the independent ones concurrently at
# the end of the block, and the batch is resolved into a list of results.
#
#let scheduled = autonomous(batch(
#    realise(instantiate($e1)),
#    realise(instantiate($e2)),
#    realise(instantiate($e3))
#))

markdown^(
# Step-4 coordination primitives

- batch group (unforced): `$bundle`
- batch forced (collects all): $collected
- any group (first winner): `$first`

A `Group` is a control value: spliced raw it renders as a marker (above), and
forced with `now(...)` it resolves per its topology mode — `batch`/`all`
collect every result into a list, while `any`/`race` yield a single winner.
)_markdown
